<div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"><br />doesn't have infinite endurance<br /></div><br /><br />I've assumed this is the reason for using battery RAM on some games instead of flash, because there are frequent updates to saved data (F-Zero X for N64 has battery RAM, since I think the game updates stats every race). Another nice benefit of using battery RAM is that any spare space can be used as extra work memory (or you could even use a larger RAM). I think Yoshi's Island for SNES did this.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Mon Sep 04, 2006 2:06 pm</p><hr />
